'''''Uj'ayl''''' was a sticky, sweet [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] syrup.<ref name="Revelation">''[[Legacy of the Force: Revelation]]''</ref> Used in Mandalorian cooking,<ref name="Karen Traviss Site">{{WebCite|url=http://www.karentraviss.com/page20/page26/index|text=''Mando'a'' dictionary|work=Karen Traviss|archiveurl=https://archive.is/4jOyY}}</ref> the scented ''uj'ayl'' syrup was most commonly used as an ingredient in the creation of [[Uj'alayi/Legends|''uj'alayi'']], a flat, dense cake.<ref name="TMPaC">{{InsiderCite|86|The Mandalorians: People and Culture}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
''Uj'ayl'' was first introduced to ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]] in the [[2006]] ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' article, ''[[The Mandalorians: People and Culture]]'', by [[Karen Traviss]]. It was later mentioned in Traviss' [[2008]] entry into the multi-[[Author/Legends|author]] ''[[Star Wars: Legacy of the Force]]'' novel series, ''[[Legacy of the Force: Revelation]]''.

The ''Star Wars Insider'' article featured the Mandalorian syrup as "uj'jayl", with two instances of the letter J. However, the [http://www.karentraviss.com/page20/page26/index ''Mando'a'' dictionary] provided by Karen Traviss on her website uses the spelling "uj'ayl", with only a single J. Due to a similar change in spelling involving [[Black ale/Legends|''ne'tra gal'']], and the fact that the latest iteration of the ''Mando'a'' dictionary is the most recent source, this article makes use of the second spelling.

